NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The reason for that is when it goes 1N-P-P, the points are pretty evenly spread. If 4th seat has fewer points, that implies 2nd seat has more points. And it is better for 2nd seat to have more HCP, as they are sitting behind the NT bidder.|
PG| ***** 17 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Balancing is very misunderstood. I know a lot of teachers say "borrow a king from partner" and add that to your HCP to see if you should balance. But that is not really correct. A better way to look at it is that the points are evenly spread. |
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, in balancing seat, if you have fewer points, pard has more points. When balancing you are bidding based on the partnership assets, not just what is in your hand. |
